<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 09 at 3:02PM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Moderate to heavy snow will the Madison Valley through 400 PM
MST...
At 259 PM MST, moderate to heavy snow was occurring over the Madison
Valley.
HAZARD...Moderate to heavy snow.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Reduced visibility down to a half mile or less and slippery
roads.
Locations impacted include...
Ennis, Cameron, and Jeffers.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>Slow Down and be prepared for reduced visibility and slippery roads.</instruction>
